## ⚙️ Discord Developer Portal Setup (Prerequisite)

Before running the code, you need to create a bot account on Discord and invite it to your server. Follow these steps:

### 1. Create an Application
1. Go to the [Discord Developer Portal](https://discord.com/developers/applications) and log in with your Discord account.
2. Click the **"New Application"** button in the top right corner.
3. Give your bot a name (e.g., "MemeBot") and click **"Create"**.

### 2. Set Up the Bot
1. In the left sidebar, click on the **"Bot"** tab.
2. Here, you can change your bot's username and upload a profile picture.
3. Scroll down to the **"Privileged Gateway Intents"** section.
4. Toggle on the **"Message Content Intent"** (This is crucial; without it, the bot cannot read what users type).
5. Click the green **"Save Changes"** button at the bottom.

### 3. Get Your Token
1. Still on the **"Bot"** tab, scroll up to the "Token" section.
2. Click the **"Reset Token"** button to generate your unique password.
3. Copy this token. **Warning:** Treat this token like your bank password. Never share it with anyone or upload it publicly to GitHub.

### 4. Invite the Bot to Your Server
1. In the left sidebar, click on **"OAuth2"**, then select **"URL Generator"**.
2. Under "Scopes", check the box for **`bot`**.
3. Scroll down to "Bot Permissions" and check **`Administrator`** (or just select `Send Messages` and `Read Message History` for basic needs).
4. Copy the generated URL at the bottom of the page.
5. Paste that URL into your web browser, select your Discord server from the dropdown list, and click "Authorize".

Your bot is now resting offline in your server! Now you can proceed to the setup steps below to bring it online.
